Dangerous policy:
{"Effect":"Allow","Action":"*","Resource":"*"}

This grants full access to every AWS service and resource. If the Lambda is compromised, the attacker has complete control of the AWS account: they can delete all data, create expensive resources, exfiltrate data from any service, and modify IAM to maintain access.

Least-privilege replacement:
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": ["s3:GetObject"],
      "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::my-bucket/input/*"
    },
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": ["dynamodb:PutItem", "dynamodb:UpdateItem"],
      "Resource": "arn:aws:dynamodb:us-east-1:123456789012:table/my-table"
    },
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": ["logs:CreateLogGroup", "logs:CreateLogStream", "logs:PutLogEvents"],
      "Resource": "arn:aws:logs:us-east-1:123456789012:*"
    }
  ]
}
